description: "Initially, the main objective of Remarkable is to port all Shoulda macros to RSpec, but of course the plan is more ambitious than that. I have other ideas that will hopefully be especially useful for Rspec users.  At this point you may ask: \xE2\x80\x9CBut aren\xE2\x80\x99t there already plug-ins that do the same thing. Why build something else?\xE2\x80\x9D  First, this isn\xE2\x80\x99t simply \xE2\x80\x9Canother\xE2\x80\x9D plugin with RSpec matchers. It also does a lot of things differently that I feel are better than other approaches."
